At least one person was killed when two trucks collided and caught alight on the R705 in Jacobsdal in the Free State on Saturday night, paramedics said.
When ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at 10.15pm they found two trucks engulfed in flames, ER24 spokeswoman Ineke van Huyssteen said on Sunday.
“Upon further assessment, paramedics found one person who was killed. At this stage it is uncertain if there were more fatalities. The police will be conducting an investigation,” she said.
– African News Agency (ANA)